"[\"Whether employees have the right to access their personnel files is most often determined by state law. \", \"Most states have laws regarding access rights. These laws usually explain the records an employee may have access to as well as the limitations of that access. Some states also have \\u201copen records\\u201d laws that allow certain parts of government employees\\u2019 personnel files to be publicly accessible. Certain states do not have laws addressing access rights, in which case the employer may create its own policy. The employer must then consistently follow its written policy and should  document all policy changes in writing.\", \"If you have employees in multiple states, you may need to create separate policies regarding personnel files for employees in each state, in order to comply with all applicable laws. \", \"\", \"\"]"